org.jamwiki.model

Class Namespace

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jamwiki.model.Namespace
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class Namespace
extends Object
implements Serializable
    Namespaces allow the organization of wiki topics by dividing topics into groups. A namespace will precede the topic, such as "Namespace:Topic". Namespaces can be customized by modifying using configuration tools, but the namesapces defined as constants always exist and are required for wiki operation.

        public Integer getMainNamespaceId()

        public boolean isCaseSensitive()
        Certain namespaces are case sensitive (such as the main namespace) while others (such as the user namespace) are not.

      • findCommentsNamespace

        public static Namespace findCommentsNamespace(Namespace namespace)
                                       throws DataAccessException
        Given a namespace, return the Namespace for the corresponding "comments" namespace. If no match exists return null. Example: if this method is called with Namespace.USER_COMMENTS or Namespace.USER as an argument, Namespace.USER_COMMENTS will be returned.
        Throws:
        DataAccessException

      • findMainNamespace

        public static Namespace findMainNamespace(Namespace namespace)
        Given a namespace, return the Namespace for the "main" (ie, not comments) namespace. If no match exists return null. Example: if this method is called with Namespace.USER_COMMENTS or Namespace.USER as an argument, Namespace.USER will be returned.

      • namespace

        public static Namespace namespace(int namespaceId)
        Utility method for retrieving a namespace given the ID. Note that this method will suppress any database exceptions, so if the caller must know if the retrieval failed then DataHandler.lookupNamespaceById() should be used instead.
        Parameters:
        namespaceId - The ID of the namespace being retrieved.
        Returns:
        The Namespace object that matches the ID, or null if no match is found or if an error is returned.

      • retrieveDefaultNamespacesForSetup

        public static Namespace[] retrieveDefaultNamespacesForSetup()
        Return a list of the default namespaces for use by setup. Note that this method exists solely for setup.

      • equals

        public boolean equals(Namespace namespace)
        Standard equals method. Two namespaces are equal if they have the same ID.
